    "slug": "237-candidates-pass-2026-somali-bar-exam",
    "summary": "The Somali Bar Exam Committee announced that 237 out of 276 candidates passed the 2026 exam held on July 2, with an 85.9% success rate.",
    "content": "Mogadishu, July 21, 2026 – The Somali Bar Exam Committee released the final results for the 2026 Bar Examination on Monday. The test was administered on July 2 to 276 candidates, who sat for the exam out of a total of 302 registered applicants. According to the committee, 237 candidates successfully passed, representing an overall pass rate of 85.9%. Meanwhile, 39 candidates failed, accounting for 14.1% of those who took the test. The committee also noted that 26 registered candidates did not attend the examination.\n\nOf the 174 male candidates who participated, 149 passed, while 88 female candidates took the exam and 88 passed, making the female pass rate 100%. This marks a notable achievement for female legal professionals in Somalia. The rigorous selection process aims to ensure only qualified individuals enter the legal profession.\n\nFor diaspora Somalis, this development holds particular relevance. Many in the diaspora pursue legal careers abroad and may consider returning to Somalia to practice. The transparent release of results and high pass rate signal improved governance in Somalia's legal sector, potentially encouraging diaspora lawyers to engage with the country's judicial system, whether through advisory roles, training, or direct practice.\n\nAdditionally, the results reflect ongoing efforts to professionalize Somalia's legal system, which has historically faced challenges due to instability. A growing pool of certified lawyers strengthens the rule of law and boosts investor confidence, key factors for diaspora members considering business or legal partnerships in Somalia.\n\nRead the original report from Goobjoog here: https://goobjoog.com/2026/07/21/237-murashax-oo-gudbay-imtixaanka-qareennimada-2026/",
    "source": "goobjoog.com",
